			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Variant on the damage shield trick...most damage shields are level limited.  You can't get the good DS's on until you get pretty high up.  A better way to use DS's goes like this.  (I call it Playing Porcupine).
<br />

<br />
1.  The person who is DOING the PLing should cast a low level DS on himself.   This gives him enough aggro to keep the mobs on him, but doesn't kill the mobs so fast that the other person doesn't get the chance to damage the mobs.
<br />

<br />
2.  Have the person doing the PLing pull a number of mobs.  Takes a little practice in PLing to know how many greenies in each zone you can take getting beat on without dying.
<br />

<br />
3.  Train the mobs back to the person being PL'ed.
<br />

<br />
4.  Let the person being PL'ed  do a small amount of damage to each mob.  (A low level AoE spell works great for this if you've got it...for rangers, that low level lightening spell is great).
<br />

<br />
5.  Once all of the mobs have each been damaged by the person being PL'ed, let the person PLing cast his best DS ON HIMSELF.  He normally will still have aggro...that's why he had the small DS on first.  Now just stand back and let the mobs wear themselves out on the DS.
<br />

<br />
Remember this works great if you're also a healing class (this is how I PL with my high level druid).  And if you team up with some of the other classes (high level chanter) you'd be amazed at what you can do.  For example...have a high level chanter cast Fire Elemental Illusion on the druid...then the druid can have THREE DS's going at one time...the "coat" one, the "shield" one, and the one provided by FE form...and they all stack!  Couple that with druid heals and the enchanter's rune spells...you can PL up into the lower 50s.
<br />

<br />
I agree with other posters here tho...remember the more you're PL'ed...the longer your going to spend trying to FIX those skills.  Spell skills are easy...sit around in PoK with a C on, casting your lowest level spells.  Melee skills you can get up if in a group, if they're very understanding about your initial lameness.</span><span class="gentblsmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
